    {
      "letter": "b",
      "prompt": "For what value of the constant $k$ does $f$ have a critical point at $x = 1$? For this value of $k$, determine whether $f$ has a relative minimum, relative maximum, or neither at $x = 1$. Justify your answer.",
      "point_value": 3,
      "scoring_notes": "f'(1) = 0 => 2k + 1 = 0 => k = -1/2. Then f''(1) = 2(-1/2) - 1 = -2 < 0, so relative maximum at x=1.",
